\begin_layout Subsubsection
Sigma model
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From Wikipedia, the sigma model Lagrangain can be written as
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{L}\left(\phi_{1},\cdots,\phi_{n}\right)=\frac{1}{2}\sum_{ij}g_{ij}d\phi^{i}\wedge*d\phi^{j}-V\left(\phi\right)
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{ij}$
\end_inset

 is a Riemannian metric on the field space 
\begin_inset Formula $\Phi$
\end_inset

.
 Equivalently, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{L}=\frac{1}{2}g_{ij}\left(\phi\right)\left(\partial^{\mu}\phi^{i}\right)\left(\partial_{\mu}\phi^{j}\right)-V\left(\phi\right)
\]

\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial_{\mu}\phi$
\end_inset

 is a section of the jet bundle of 
\begin_inset Formula $M\times\Phi$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Matrix identities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yilmaz
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
